Counter-controlled repetition is also known as:
Correct Answer
  Definite repetition 
  Indefinite repetition 
You Answered
  Multiple-repetition structure 
  Double-repetition structure 
 
Question 16
1 / 1 pts
How many times is the body of the loop below executed?
int counter;
counter = 1;
while (counter > 20)

{

// body of loop

counter = counter - 1;

} // end while
  19. 
  20. 
  21. 
Correct!
  0. 
 
Question 17
1 / 1 pts
Which statement is true?
  Dividing two integers results in integer division. 
  With integer division, any fractional part of the calculation is lost. 
  With integer division, any fractional part of the calculation is truncated. 
Correct!
  All of these. 
 
